section.p:
The voice was unwelcome– 
      except, Rathe thought, 
      of all the people here, Guis Forveijl is the person most likely to know where I can find Chresta Aconin. “Guis.”

Rathe took the folded paper, its edges a little damp from the snow, frowning as he recognized b’Estorr’s elegant hand. It was only a few lines, and he swore under his breath as he took in the sense of them. b’Estorr was still searching for a phytomancer who was willing to take the Alphabet seriously enough to help them; 
      if I haven’t found one by second sunrise, he finished, 
      I’ll come myself and do what little I can.
